15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-146 of Title 70, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. An Oklahoma charter school that reaches a district composite
20 academic achievement score within ten (10) points of the state
21 average composite academic achievement score, as published in the
22 Oklahoma State Report Card, shall receive One Hundred Thousand
23 Dollars ($100,000.00) to be used for lease payments, rental
24 facilities for student testing, transportation, or student services.
Req. No. 12613 Page 1

1 B. The funds described in subsection A of this section shall be
2 subject to the availability of funds and shall be in addition to
3 other funds the district may receive or is eligible to receive.
4 C. The composite academic achievement score calculated two
5 years prior shall be used to determine the current fiscal year's
6 recipients of the funds described in subsection A of this section.
7 For example, the composite academic achievement scores for the 2022-
8 2023 school year shall determine which districts are eligible to
9 receive the funds for the 2025 fiscal year.
10 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
11 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
12 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
13 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
14 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
